summary: Da Vinci's hand impairment caused by nerve damage, not stroke
title: Da Vinci's hand impairment caused by nerve damage, not stroke
body:
Da Vinci’s hand impairment caused by nerve damage, not stroke

A fainting episode causing traumatic nerve damage affecting his right hand could be why Leonardo da Vinci’s painting skills were hampered in his late career. While the impairment affected his ability to hold palettes and brushes to paint with his right hand, he was able to continue teaching and drawing with his left hand. According to most authors, the origin of da Vinci’s right hand palsy was…

summary: Toxic chemicals in ocean algae could be causing Alzheimer’s-like disease in DOLPHINS, study warns In the paper, researchers say...
caption: Toxic chemicals in ocean algae could be causing Alzheimer’s-like disease in DOLPHINS, study warns In the paper, researchers say detectable amounts of the toxin BMAA – found in harmful algal blooms – was observed for the first time in the brains and bodies of 13 of the 14 dolphins studied.
